- Use functional components with hooks instead of class components
- Implement proper state management using Context API or state management libraries
- Utilize memoization techniques like `useMemo` and `useCallback` for performance optimization
- Follow the single responsibility principle for components
- Implement proper error boundaries for error handling
- Use proper prop types and TypeScript interfaces for component props
- Keep components small and focused on a single responsibility
- Implement proper loading and error states for async operations 